## Sending Data Back

When a function reaches the `return` keyword, it immediately outputs whatever value follows it, and sends it directly back to the spot where the function was called.

```javascript
function addNumbers(a, b) {
  let sum = a + b;
  return sum; // Send the answer out!
}

// The function becomes its returned answer!
let myAnswer = addNumbers(5, 5);
console.log(myAnswer); // 10
```

Think of the function call as a placeholder. `addNumbers(5, 5)` literally vanishes and gets replaced by `10`!

