## Return ALWAYS Ends the Function

The `return` keyword is identical to the `break` keyword in a loop. 

The very millisecond JavaScript hits a `return` statement, **the function is destroyed**, the value is sent back, and no further lines inside the function will execute!

```javascript
function testFunction() {
  return "I am done!";
  console.log("This will NEVER run.");
  console.log("The function died on line 2.");
}
```
